UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1566
1 AN ACT relating to outdoor recreation.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF SUBCHAPTER 12 OF KRS CHAPTER
4 154 IS CREATED TO READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) There is created in the Cabinet for Economic Development the Office of Outdoor
6 Recreation Industry, which shall:
7 (a) Serve as coordinator for Kentucky's outdoor industry matters, including
8 resource development and industry promotion, and foster connections
9 between constituents, businesses, and communities that rely on Kentucky's
10 outdoor recreation economy;
11 (b) Make policy recommendations to the Governor and the Legislative
12 Research Commission on outdoor recreation industry matters, including
13 business issues unique to the outdoor recreation industry; and
14 (c) Coordinate and support the outdoor recreation industry in Kentucky to
15 promote economic development, conservation, stewardship, education,
16 workforce training, and public health and wellness.
17 (2) The office shall be headed by an executive director appointed by the secretary
18 pursuant to KRS 154.l0-050, who shall be the administrative head and chief
19 executive officer.
20 (3) The secretary shall have authority to hire staff, contract for services, expend
21 funds, and operate the normal business activities of the office.
22 Section 2. KRS 12.020 is amended to read as follows:
23 Departments, program cabinets and their departments, and the respective major
24 administrative bodies that they include are enumerated in this section. It is not intended
25 that this enumeration of administrative bodies be all-inclusive. Every authority, board,
26 bureau, interstate compact, commission, committee, conference, council, office, or any
27 other form of organization shall be included in or attached to the department or program
